- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0005-97b95c20
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0005
  scope:
    actor:
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure that would violate subpart requirements
  conditions:
  - '"in a manner that would violate the requirements of this subpart, if done by
    the covered entity"'
  exceptions:
  - '"except for the purposes specified under § 164.504(e)(2)(i)(A) or (B) if such
    uses or disclosures are permitted by its contract or other arrangement."'
  requirements:
  - Do not use or disclose protected health information in a manner that would violate
    the requirements of this subpart if done by the covered entity.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Prohibits business-associate PHI disclosures contrary to the HIPAA subpart;
      verifiable by inspecting disclosures, logs, contracts, and PHI metadata.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - log_check
    - config_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0005-7e7518b2
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0005
  scope:
    actor:
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure outside contract or law
  conditions:
  - unless permitted by its business associate contract or other arrangement pursuant
    to § 164.504(e)
  - unless required by law
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Do not use or disclose protected health information except as permitted by its
    business associate contract or other arrangement pursuant to § 164.504(e) or as
    required by law.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: PHI disclosure is detectable, but verifying permission under contract
      or law requires external legal/contract evidence not objectively checkable here.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - data_check
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0005-f3649c7d
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0005
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: denial of individual's access to PHI
  conditions:
  - when requested under § 164.524 or § 164.528
  - when request is "required by § 164.524 or § 164.528"
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Disclose protected health information to an individual when requested under, and
    required by, § 164.524 or § 164.528.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligation to disclose PHI upon authorized request; verifiable by inspecting
      access-request/disclosure logs or system I/O.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0005-ad335414
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0005
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: failure to provide PHI for compliance investigation
  conditions:
  - when required by the Secretary under subpart C of part 160 to investigate or determine
    the covered entity's compliance with this subchapter
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Disclose protected health information to the Secretary under subpart C of part
    160 when required to investigate or determine the covered entity's compliance
    with this subchapter.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligation to disclose PHI when required is verifiable by inspecting disclosure/audit
      logs or transmitted outputs for PHI sent to the Secretary.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0006-5e1d5b16
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0006
  scope:
    actor:
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized withholding of PHI from oversight or authorized requestors
  conditions:
  - when required by the Secretary under subpart C of part 160 to investigate or determine
    the business associate's compliance with this subchapter
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The business associate shall disclose protected health information when required
    by the Secretary under subpart C of part 160 to investigate or determine the business
    associate's compliance with this subchapter.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Can be verified by checking audit/runtime logs for Secretary request events
      and corresponding PHI disclosure actions.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0006-aa8c540b
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0006
  scope:
    actor:
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: failure to provide electronic copies of PHI to satisfy individual's request
  conditions:
  - as necessary to satisfy a covered entity's obligations under § 164.524(c)(2)(ii)
    and (3)(ii) with respect to an individual's request for an electronic copy of
    protected health information
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The business associate shall disclose protected health information to the covered
    entity, individual, or the individual's designee as necessary to satisfy a covered
    entity's obligations under § 164.524(c)(2)(ii) and (3)(ii) with respect to an
    individual's request for an electronic copy of protected health information.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligation to disclose PHI for electronic copy requests is concrete and
      verifiable via logs or I/O showing disclosure events and recipients.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0006-682a8c9f
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0006
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized use or disclosure of genetic PHI for underwriting
  conditions:
  - for underwriting purposes
  exceptions:
  - excluding an issuer of a long-term care policy falling within paragraph (1)(viii)
    of the definition of health plan
  requirements:
  - The entity shall not use or disclose protected health information that is genetic
    information for underwriting purposes.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Prohibition is specific (entity, genetic PHI, underwriting); use/disclosure
      can be detected via logs or dataset metadata.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0008-2c30b064
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0008
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - Except pursuant to and in compliance with § 164.508(a)(4)
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Entity and business associate must not sell protected health information.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Explicit prohibition on selling PHI; can be audited via logs, policies/configs,
      contracts, and dataset metadata for sale transactions.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - config_check
    - repo_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0008-8d5cb930
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0008
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Entity and business associate must treat a disclosure of protected health information
    as a sale when the covered entity or business associate directly or indirectly
    receives remuneration from or on behalf of the recipient in exchange for the protected
    health information.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Verify logs/datasets showing PHI disclosure and corresponding remuneration
      to determine if treated as a sale.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0010-c59b13d2
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0010
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: PHI used to investigate individuals for seeking reproductive health care
  conditions:
  - use or disclose protected health information
  - to conduct a criminal, civil, or administrative investigation
  - for the mere act of seeking, obtaining, providing, or facilitating reproductive
    health care
  - subject to paragraphs (a)(5)(iii)(B) and (C) of this section
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider and business associate must not use or disclose protected health information
    to conduct a criminal, civil, or administrative investigation into any person
    for the mere act of seeking, obtaining, providing, or facilitating reproductive
    health care.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Prohibits providers/business associates from disclosing PHI for investigations;
      check disclosure logs and PHI metadata for investigation-purpose reproductive-care
      disclosures.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0010-b585c5a0
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0010
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: PHI used to identify persons for investigation or liability related to reproductive
    health care
  conditions:
  - use or disclose protected health information
  - to identify any person
  - for any purpose described in paragraphs (a)(5)(iii)(A)(1) or (2) of this section
  - subject to paragraphs (a)(5)(iii)(B) and (C) of this section
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider and business associate must not use or disclose protected health information
    to identify any person for any purpose described in paragraphs (a)(5)(iii)(A)(1)
    or (2) of this section.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Prohibits providers/BAs from disclosing PHI to identify persons; detect
      via inspecting model/app I/O or runtime logs for identifying PHI disclosures
      and purpose.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0011-3a457aac
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0011
  scope:
    actor:
    - business associate
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure related to reproductive health
  conditions:
  - request for protected health information in connection with any person seeking,
    obtaining, providing, or facilitating reproductive health care
  - 'one or more of the following exists: (1) the reproductive health care is lawful
    under the law of the state in which such health care is provided under the circumstances
    in which it is provided; (2) the reproductive health care is protected, required,
    or authorized by Federal law under the circumstances in which it is provided;
    (3) the presumption at paragraph (a)(5)(iii)(C) of this section applies'
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - When a covered entity or business associate receives a request for protected health
    information in connection with reproductive health care, the business associate
    and provider shall reasonably determine that at least one of the listed conditions
    (lawful under state law; protected/required/authorized by Federal law; presumption
    at paragraph (a)(5)(iii)(C) applies) exists before treating the prohibition at
    paragraph (a)(5)(iii)(A) as applicable.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: 'Verify via I/O tests: supply requests with known legal conditions, check
      responses/refusals and recorded determinations.'
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - log_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0012-5ee6386e
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0012
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - reproductive health care provided by another person
  - under paragraph (a)(5)(iii)(B)(1) or (2)
  exceptions:
  - actual knowledge that the reproductive health care was not lawful under the circumstances
    in which it was provided
  - factual information supplied by the person requesting the use or disclosure of
    protected health information that demonstrates a substantial factual basis that
    the reproductive health care was not lawful under the specific circumstances in
    which it was provided
  requirements:
  - The provider or business associate must presume that reproductive health care
    provided by another person is lawful under paragraph (a)(5)(iii)(B)(1) or (2)
    unless they have actual knowledge or factual information demonstrating the reproductive
    health care was not lawful under the specific circumstances in which it was provided.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Requires subjective legal judgment about 'actual knowledge' or 'substantial
      factual basis'—no single objective artifact to definitively verify.
    evidence_signals: []
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0013-6a47068e
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0013
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: excessive PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - when using or disclosing protected health information
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - A covered entity or business associate must make reasonable efforts to limit protected
    health information to the minimum necessary for the purpose when using or disclosing
    it.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: '''Reasonable efforts'' and ''minimum necessary'' are subjective; no objective
      pass/fail predicate provided for verification.'
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - log_check
    - config_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0014-f243d769
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0014
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - agreed to a restriction pursuant to § 164.522(a)(1)
  exceptions:
  - as otherwise provided in § 164.522(a)
  requirements:
  - Entity may not use or disclose the protected health information covered by the
    restriction in violation of such restriction.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Prohibition on disclosing restricted PHI is verifiable via access logs,
      PHI dataset tags, and restriction policy/config inspection.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - data_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0017-379d2646
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0017
  scope:
    actor:
    - business associate
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - satisfactory assurances required by paragraph (e)(1) of this section
  - subcontractor will create, receive, maintain, or transmit protected health information
    on behalf of the business associate
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The business associate must document the satisfactory assurances required by paragraph
    (e)(1) through a written contract or other written agreement or arrangement that
    meets the applicable requirements of § 164.504(e).
  evidence:
  - written contract or other written agreement or arrangement
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Existence of a written contract/arrangement meeting §164.504(e) can be
      verified by inspecting organizational contract records.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0018-4a858b7e
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0018
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context:
    - regulated
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - for a period of 50 years following the death of the individual
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The provider must comply with the requirements of this subpart with respect to
    the protected health information of a deceased individual for a period of 50 years
    following the individual's death.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Requires providers to protect deceased individuals' PHI for 50 years;
      verifiable via retention metadata, access controls/config, or audit logs.
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
    - config_check
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0018-3f95beb4
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0018
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context:
    - regulated
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - as specified in this paragraph
  exceptions:
  - except as provided in paragraphs (g)(3) and (g)(5) of this section
  requirements:
  - The provider must treat a personal representative as the individual for purposes
    of this subchapter.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligation to treat personal representatives as the individual; verifiable
      via access-control/config mappings or logs/I/O showing identical disclosure
      decisions.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
    - log_check
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0019-0817e761
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0019
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - under applicable law the person has authority to act on behalf of an individual
    who is an adult or an emancipated minor in making decisions related to health
    care
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The provider must treat a person who under applicable law has authority to act
    on behalf of an adult or an emancipated minor in making health care decisions
    as a personal representative under this subchapter with respect to protected health
    information relevant to such personal representation.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Verifying a person “has authority under applicable law” requires external
      legal proof not observable from system artifacts alone.
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0019-ef82a103
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0019
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - under applicable law a parent, guardian, or other person acting in loco parentis
    has authority to act on behalf of an unemancipated minor in making decisions related
    to health care
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The provider must treat a parent, guardian, or other person acting in loco parentis
    who has such authority as the personal representative of the unemancipated minor
    with respect to protected health information relevant to such personal representation.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Verify via records and logs that a parent/guardian was documented as personal
      representative and PHI disclosures occurred accordingly.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - log_check
    - config_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0019-ba1d0af2
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-502-uses-and-disclosures-of-protected-health-information/sent_0019
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - a parent, guardian, or person acting in loco parentis assents to an agreement
    of confidentiality between the covered health care provider and the minor with
    respect to the health care service
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The provider must not treat the parent, guardian, or person acting in loco parentis
    as the personal representative of the unemancipated minor with respect to protected
    health information pertaining to that health care service when such a confidentiality
    agreement has been assented to.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: 'Verifyable by audit: check confidentiality-agreement records plus access-control
      settings and disclosure/access logs for any PHI shared with parent/guardian.'
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
    - config_check
    - log_check
    - io_check
