    reason: Requires legal/semantic judgment of 'not inconsistent'; no objective pass/fail
      predicate for artifact inspection.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0011-19feece6
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements/sent_0011
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - unless receipt of a certification by the plan sponsor that the plan documents
    have been amended to incorporate the required provisions and that the plan sponsor
    agrees to provisions (A) through (H)
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Do not disclose protected health information to the plan sponsor unless the group
    health plan has received a certification by the plan sponsor that the plan documents
    have been amended and the plan sponsor agrees to the specified provisions (A)
    through (H).
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Requires checking for certification and amended plan documents; their
      presence and contents are objectively verifiable in stored records.
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0011-0648b136
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements/sent_0011
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - with respect to protected health information received from the group health plan
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Not use or further disclose the protected health information other than as permitted
    or required by the plan documents or as required by law.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: PHI disclosures can be detected in logs/dataset tags and compared against
      plan documents/authorization records.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - config_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0011-699a6bd5
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements/sent_0011
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure by agents
  conditions:
  - when providing protected health information received from the group health plan
    to agents
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Ensure that any agents to whom the plan sponsor provides protected health information
    agree to the same restrictions and conditions that apply to the plan sponsor with
    respect to such information.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Check for agreements/records listing agents and verify PHI transfer logs
      show recipients are only agents with those agreements.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0011-dcb327ac
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements/sent_0011
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: undetected improper PHI disclosures
  conditions:
  - if the plan sponsor becomes aware of a use or disclosure of protected health information
    that is inconsistent with the permitted uses or disclosures provided for
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Report to the group health plan any use or disclosure of the protected health
    information that is inconsistent with the uses or disclosures provided for of
    which the plan sponsor becomes aware.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligation to report inconsistent PHI disclosures can be verified by checking
      audit logs or outgoing report messages.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0011-7e85d9d9
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements/sent_0011
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: undetected noncompliant PHI uses or disclosures
  conditions:
  - for purposes of determining compliance by the group health plan with 45 CFR Part
    164 Subpart E
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Make internal practices, books, and records relating to the use and disclosure
    of protected health information received from the group health plan available
    to the Secretary for purposes of determining compliance by the group health plan
    with 45 CFR Part 164 Subpart E.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Clause lacks a specified observable artifact or verification mechanism
      (no logs, delivery receipts, or record identifiers to check).
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0012-e1e5f35b
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements/sent_0012
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - when no longer needed for the purpose for which disclosure was made
  - if feasible
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The organization must return or destroy all protected health information received
    from the group health plan that it still maintains in any form and retain no copies
    of such information.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Can verify by checking data inventories/metadata and deletion/return logs
      to confirm no PHI copies remain.
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0012-21ca403e
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements/sent_0012
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - when no longer needed for the purpose for which disclosure was made
  - if return or destruction is not feasible
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - If return or destruction of the protected health information is not feasible,
    the organization must limit further uses and disclosures to those purposes that
    make the return or destruction infeasible.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: No objective rule to identify which 'purposes' make return/destruction
      infeasible; requires subjective judgment or defined purpose codes.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - log_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0012-c20ebcee
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements/sent_0012
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The organization must ensure that the plan documents describe those employees,
    classes of employees, or other persons under the control of the plan sponsor who
    are to be given access to the protected health information to be disclosed.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Requires plan documents to list employees/classes with PHI access — verifiable
      by inspecting the plan documents or policy files.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0012-6aa17526
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements/sent_0012
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - for employees described in paragraph (f)(2)(iii)(A)
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The organization must restrict the access to and use by the employees and other
    persons described in paragraph (f)(2)(iii)(A) to the plan administration functions
    that the plan sponsor performs for the group health plan.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Access can be verified via access-control configs and audit logs ensuring
      specified personnel access only plan-administration functions.
    evidence_signals:
    - config_check
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0012-6e995a61
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-504-uses-and-disclosures-organizational-requirements/sent_0012
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - for persons described in paragraph (f)(2)(iii)(A)
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The organization must provide an effective mechanism for resolving any issues
    of noncompliance by persons described in paragraph (f)(2)(iii)(A) with the plan
    document provisions required by this paragraph.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Requires a subjective standard ('effective mechanism') and lacks objective
      success criteria or required artifacts to allow automated pass/fail.
    evidence_signals:
