- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0002-2d2fa3bd
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r/sent_0002
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - when an authorization under § 164.508 is required
  - when another condition must be met for such use or disclosure to be permissible
    under this subpart
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - entity must not treat consent under paragraph (b) as effective to permit a use
    or disclosure of protected health information.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Prohibits relying on paragraph (b) consent; verifiable by inspecting disclosures
      and logs for uses/disclosures based on that consent.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0004-3e7070da
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r/sent_0004
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - without an authorization that is valid under this section
  exceptions:
  - Except as otherwise permitted or required by this subchapter
  requirements:
  - provider must not use or disclose protected health information without an authorization
    that is valid under this section.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Requires legal judgment of whether an authorization is 'valid' and 'use'
      is ambiguous; no single objective oracle to decide pass/fail.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - data_check
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0005-88236085
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r/sent_0005
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized disclosure of psychotherapy notes
  conditions: []
  exceptions:
  - Use by the originator of the psychotherapy notes for treatment
  - Use or disclosure by the covered entity for its own training programs in which
    students, trainees, or practitioners in mental health learn under supervision
    to practice or improve their skills in group, joint, family, or individual counseling
  - Use or disclosure by the covered entity to defend itself in a legal action or
    other proceeding brought by the individual
  - A use or disclosure that is required by § 164.502(a)(2)(ii) or permitted by §
    164.512(a); § 164.512(d) with respect to the oversight of the originator of the
    psychotherapy notes; § 164.512(g)(1); or § 164.512(j)(1)(i)
  requirements:
  - The covered entity must obtain an authorization for any use or disclosure of psychotherapy
    notes.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Requires authorization for any psychotherapy-note disclosure; existence
      of authorizations and disclosure events can be checked in logs or data records.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0005-d5edc9c7
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r/sent_0005
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized disclosure of PHI for marketing
  conditions: []
  exceptions:
  - Face-to-face communication made by a covered entity to an individual
  - A promotional gift of nominal value provided by the covered entity
  requirements:
  - The covered entity must obtain an authorization for any use or disclosure of protected
    health information for marketing.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Authorization for marketing disclosures can be verified by inspecting
      disclosure logs and consent/authorization records tied to PHI marketing events.
    evidence_signals:
    - log_check
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0006-a868254a
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r/sent_0006
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: undisclosed remuneration for PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - marketing involves financial remuneration to the covered entity from a third party
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Entity must include in the authorization a statement that such remuneration is
    involved when the marketing involves financial remuneration to the covered entity
    from a third party.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Can inspect the authorization text to verify inclusion of a remuneration
      statement when third‑party marketing payment occurs.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0006-c739744b
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r
