- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0009-9b92aecd
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r/sent_0009
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: unauthorized PHI disclosure
  conditions:
  - attempt to combine an authorization for use or disclosure of protected health
    information with any other document to create a compound authorization
  exceptions:
  - authorization for the use or disclosure of protected health information for a
    research study combined with any other type of written permission for the same
    or another research study (including combining with another authorization for
    the same research study; with an authorization for the creation or maintenance
    of a research database or repository; or with a consent to participate in research)
  requirements:
  - provider must not combine an authorization for the use or disclosure of protected
    health information with any other document to create a compound authorization,
    except as stated in the listed research-related exception.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Clear prohibition on providers combining PHI authorizations; verifiable
      by inspecting stored authorization documents for compound content.
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0010-ca66528e
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r/sent_0010
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: coerced research participation
  conditions:
  - where the provider has conditioned the provision of research-related treatment
    on the provision of one of the authorizations
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - provider must create any compound authorization that clearly differentiates between
    the conditioned and unconditioned components.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Vague 'clearly differentiates' lacks objective criteria; cannot be verified
      by inspection alone without explicit differentiation rules.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0010-308f8a51
  source:
