- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0010-ea00c5c0
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r/sent_0010
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: coerced authorization leading to conditioned benefits
  conditions:
  - when one authorization conditions the provision of treatment, payment, enrollment
    in a health plan, or eligibility for benefits under paragraph (b)(4) of this section
  exceptions:
  - compound authorization created in accordance with paragraph (b)(3)(i) of this
    section
  requirements:
  - entity must not combine authorizations (other than authorizations for psychotherapy
    notes) when one authorization conditions the provision of treatment, payment,
    enrollment in a health plan, or eligibility for benefits.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Can inspect stored authorization records/forms to detect combined authorizations
      that condition treatment/payment/enrollment.
    evidence_signals:
    - data_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0011-76c50c58
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-508-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-authorization-is-r/sent_0011
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain:
    - PHI
    context: []
  hazard: denial of treatment based on refusal to authorize use or disclosure of PHI
  conditions:
  - conditioning provision of treatment to an individual on the provision of an authorization
  exceptions:
  - covered health care provider may condition research-related treatment on authorization
    for use/disclosure of protected health information for such research under this
    section
  - health plan may condition enrollment or eligibility for benefits on provision
    of an authorization requested prior to an individual's enrollment in the health
    plan
  requirements:
  - entity must not condition the provision of treatment to an individual on the individual's
    provision of an authorization.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Behavioral prohibition ('must not condition treatment on authorization')
      can be verified by probing system I/O or logs for treatment refusals tied to
      authorization.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - log_check
