    - entity
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: lack of notice of conditioning policy
  conditions:
  - the information in paragraph (c)(2)(i)(A) of this section is included in the notice
    required by §164.520
  - the prohibition on conditioning of authorizations in paragraph (b)(4) of this
    section applies
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Include the statement "The covered entity may not condition treatment, payment,
    enrollment or eligibility for benefits on whether the individual signs the authorization"
    in the notice required by §164.520.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Verify the notice text contains the exact required sentence by inspecting
      the notice document or the service output.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0001-f2350198
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-509-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-attestation-is-req
    span_id: HIPAA_removed/subpart-e-privacy-of-individually-identifiable-health-inform/164-509-uses-and-disclosures-for-which-an-attestation-is-req/sent_0001
  scope:
    actor:
    - entity
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: individuals uninformed of consequences for refusing authorization
  conditions:
  - the information in paragraph (c)(2)(i)(A) of this section is included in the notice
    required by §164.520
  - in accordance with paragraph (b)(4) of this section the covered entity can condition
    treatment, enrollment in the health plan, or eligibility for benefits on failure
    to obtain such authorization
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - Include in the notice the consequences to the individual of a refusal to sign
    the authorization.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Requires notices to state consequences of refusing authorization; verifiable
      by inspecting notices/outputs for those statements.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
